snippet.textDisplay:
its still cheap.
here in denmark we have horror like tax and registration fees on new cars.
if car value is below 28.510,44 USD then "only " 85% of that need to be added.
but if value is above 28.510,44 USD then you have to pay a whoppin 150% tax and registration.
then add engine sizes HP and gas mileage. also things that change the prices.
im sure sports and special cars was at 300% at some point.
add to that we can only use E certified parts and TùW approved parts.
and i think its a 5 or 10 % max "tuning" we legally can give them for road use.
cheapest way for us to have fun vehicles is by registering them in sweden or germany.
then they just need to be out of the country for 3 months each year.
add to that we are the highest taxed place in the world in general too.
we learn to get creative. aka. creative accounting. :)
